# UI Component Libraries — Agent Reference

Before writing any UI component, animation, or layout, consult this reference to pick the right source. Always prefer pulling from these libraries over writing from scratch.

---

## 🎬 Animation-First (GSAP / Motion)

### motion-primitives
- **URL**: https://motion-primitives.com/docs
- **Best for**: Motion-based React components, entrance animations, layout transitions
- **Stack**: Motion (Framer Motion v11), Tailwind
- **Use when**: You need animated wrappers, morphing, staggered reveals

### buildui (recipes)
- **URL**: https://buildui.com/recipes
- **Best for**: Raw motion.dev code snippets — spring animations, drag, gestures
- **Use when**: You need low-level animation logic, not a pre-built component

### animate-ui
- **URL**: https://animate-ui.com/docs/components
- **Best for**: General animated UI components
- **Use when**: You want drop-in animated components without heavy setup

### 21st.dev community
- **URL**: https://21st.dev/community/components
- **Best for**: High-quality GSAP + Motion animated components from community
- **Use when**: You want polished, non-generic animated components

---

## ✨ High Quality / Niche

### fancycomponents.dev
- **URL**: https://www.fancycomponents.dev/components
- **Best for**: Highly specific, creative UI components
- **Use when**: You need something distinctive and unusual

### daddy.design
- **URL**: https://daddy.design/components
- **Best for**: Boutique, high-quality components — fewer options but exceptional craft
- **Use when**: Quality > quantity, niche interactions

### forgeui
- **URL**: https://forgeui.in/components/animated-form
- **Best for**: Animated forms and input components
- **Use when**: Building forms that need polish and motion

---

## 🧱 General Ready-to-Use (shadcn-style)

### reui
- **URL**: https://reui.io/docs/get-started
- **Best for**: Finished, production-ready components
- **Use when**: You need something working fast with minimal customization

### heroui
- **URL**: https://heroui.com/docs/react/components
- **Best for**: Full React component library
- **Use when**: You need a complete design system baseline

### daisyui
- **URL**: https://daisyui.com/components/
- **Best for**: Tailwind CSS component classes
- **Use when**: You want utility-class-based components with no JS overhead

---

## 🌌 Visual Effects / Backgrounds

### patterncraft
- **URL**: https://patterncraft.fun/
- **Best for**: Background patterns, ready to use
- **Use when**: You need decorative SVG/CSS background patterns

### aceternity ui
- **URL**: https://ui.aceternity.com/components
- **Best for**: Dramatic visual effects, glows, beams, spotlight effects
- **Use when**: Hero sections, landing page wow-factor elements

---

## 📊 Charts

### evilcharts
- **URL**: https://evilcharts.com/
- **Best for**: Chart components
- **Use when**: Building dashboards or data visualizations

---

## 🔊 Audio / Voice UI

### elevenlabs ui
- **URL**: https://ui.elevenlabs.io/docs/components
- **Best for**: Voice/audio-related UI components
- **Use when**: Building anything voice or audio-adjacent

---

## 📦 Decision Priority (follow this order)

1. **Animation needed?** → motion-primitives → animate-ui → 21st.dev
2. **Low-level animation logic?** → buildui recipes
3. **Niche/distinctive look?** → fancycomponents → daddy.design
4. **Animated form?** → forgeui
5. **Fast, production-ready?** → reui → heroui
6. **Background/visual effect?** → patterncraft → aceternity
7. **Chart?** → evilcharts
8. **Tailwind utility components?** → daisyui

---

## Agent Behavior Rules

- **Always fetch the component docs page** from the relevant library before writing implementation code
- **Never write animation logic from scratch** if motion-primitives or buildui has a recipe for it
- **Check aceternity or 21st.dev** before writing any hero section or landing page element
- When a component exists in multiple libraries, **prefer the one with Motion/GSAP** over plain CSS
- For shadcn-based projects, **check if the component already exists in shadcn/ui** before going to reui or heroui
